<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-028-227 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 460 953</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Oct 28 1991 v13 n43 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NT looks real at Comdex. (Microsoft Corp.'s Windows New Technologygraphical user interface)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Johnston, Stuart J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft Corp demonstrates its Windows NT graphical userinterface at the Comdex-Fall 1991 computer industry trade show.andO;The portable, 32-bit Windows NT, which stands for 'newtechnology,' is multitasking, runs with Windows 3.1 and needs8-Mbytes RAM.andP;  It was demonstrated on Intel Corp X86microprocessors, MIPS R4000 workstations and on the NCR System3000 Model 3450 80486-based computer that runs at almost 160 MIPS.andO;Windows NT will ship in the second half of 1992.andP;  Microsoft isalready shipping 200 to 300 copies of Windows 32-bit developmentkits to selected independent software vendors.andP;  It will beavailable on CD-ROM and floppy disk.andP;  Initial applications willrun on Windows NT, which is included in the kit, and they willalso run on a 32-bit version of Windows for MS-DOS that will shipin 1993.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Product development).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Microsoft Windows NT (Operating system) (Product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentGraphical user interfacePromotion of Product.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>